9/24/22, 5:56 PMSemester Project: Basic HTML & CSS Site https://ucdenver.instructure.com/courses/493630/assignments/13778641/13Semester Project: Basic HTML & CSS Site DueSep 13 by 11:59pmPoints80 Submittinga text entry box, a website url, or a file uploadAvailableuntil Sep 13 at 11:59pm This assignment was locked Sep 13 at 11:59pm. We will use the basic ideas covered during the first three weeks of class as you start to develop the fictitious project you'll complete in this class: a web site for either a small company, some other organization (e.g. a club) or a hobby site. All of the pages you complete in the assignments for this class will be related to this one organization so choose something to work on that you are interested in. Note:To insure that no two students work on the same website, please email me with the website you plan on building BEFORE beginning this project (see assignment for Week 1). The website will provide a variety of pages that share different types of information including: A photo page (either product photos or photos related to your club or hobby) A calendar of events Announce club or organization news Share information about the company or club Step 1:Create a basic index.html file in your text editor now similar to the one inHTML Sections(You can usehttp://jsfiddle.net/dgregg/p0ke2ab9/(http://jsfiddle.net/dgregg/p0ke2ab9/) as a starting point). It is just an “empty” file with the doctype, html, head and body and basic section tags: <header>, </header>, <nav>, </nav>, <section>, </section>, <main>, </main>, <footer>and</footer> in that order. You will want to remove: the text contained within the opening<title>and closing</title> tags all the content between the opening<main>and closing</main> tags
9/24/22, 5:56 PMSemester Project: Basic HTML & CSS Site https://ucdenver.instructure.com/courses/493630/assignments/13778642/13Save the file to your local computer. Step 2:Begin building this website by doing the following: Change the title of the page to be the title for your business or club (e.g. "Outdoor Depot - Camping, Hiking, Biking and Backpacking") Add a heading to the page - a level one heading that is the name of your business or club (e.g. "OutdoorDepot.com.") Immediately after the heading, add a short<h4> element with your best marketing type tag line for your club or business (e.g. "Your outdoor adventures begin here...") You will be making changes lines 4 and 8 in the file above - remember the words you choose for your business or club will be different than the example text I am using in this assignment!. Save the page, then double-click on the file to open it in your chosen browser. Step 3:Now lets expand the page to make it a bit more like a real page. Look at other websites like the one you are creating for ideas about what text might be appropriate on your site. Add a<h2>,element below your tag line (inside the<section> )with some text describing your club or business in more detail: (e.g. "Supporting all your family's outdoor activities" or "Where you shop for all your outdoor needs" ...).
